  "_comment": "CCF provider catalog — READ-ONLY reference of major model providers, their OpenAI/Anthropic-compatible chat endpoints, and recommended models. Onboarding and /fusion-config copy entries FROM here INTO your live providers.json. CCF refreshes this file on every update; do not edit it (edits are overwritten — edit providers.json instead). Endpoints are FULL chat-completion URLs (what the dispatcher POSTs to). Model IDs drift fast: confirm the latest at each provider's docs URL. zero_retention defaults to false (conservative) for cloud providers — flip a panelist's sensitive_ok to true only for a provider you trust not to retain/train on your data; ollama-local is true because it runs on your machine. Pre-wired defaults (zai, opencode-go, opencode-zen, claude-sub) live in providers.dist.json and are not duplicated here. Note: OAuth-only providers (e.g. Qwen portal) and providers without a public endpoint (Arcee) are omitted — the dispatcher needs an endpoint + bearer/x-api-key or a keyless host. This is a CURATED subset; for the COMPLETE live registry (121+ providers, every model with context + cost) use `ccf-models providers` / `ccf-models models <p>` / `ccf-models add <p> <model>` — it reads https://models.dev/api.json (the same DB Hermes uses).",
